{
  "title": "ISic002005. Funerary inscription for ʿbdmlqrt",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: <a href=\"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/EGNUE9CZ\">http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/EGNUE9CZ</a></div><div id=\"edition-interpretive-transliteration\" lang=\"xpu-Latn\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"xpu-Latn\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>qbr <span class=\"tei text-direction r-to-l\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;←</span><br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"ʿbd\n                    mlqrt\n                    bn \"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"ʿbd\n                    mlqrt\">ʿbd <span class=\"tei text-direction r-to-l\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;←</span><br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span>mlqrt</span>  <span class=\"tei text-direction r-to-l\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;←</span><br id=\"al4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span>b̊n̊ [<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span>  <span class=\"tei text-direction r-to-l\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;←</span></span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: <a href=\"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/EGNUE9CZ\">http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/EGNUE9CZ</a></div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic-transliteration\" lang=\"xpu-Latn\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"xpu-Latn\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>QBR<span class=\"tei text-direction r-to-l\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;←</span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"ʿbd\n                    mlqrt\n                    bn \"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"ʿbd\n                    mlqrt\">ʿBD<span class=\"tei text-direction r-to-l\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;←</span><br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span>MLQRT</span><span class=\"tei text-direction r-to-l\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;←</span><br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span>̊̊[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span><span class=\"tei text-direction r-to-l\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;←</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic002005_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic002005_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic002005.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic002005-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>Text of De Simone after Campus 2020</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7393-1952\">Rossana De Simone</a></p>  <p>Tomb of ʿbd mlqrt son of [---]</p>  </div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>Italian translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7393-1952\">Rossana De Simone</a></p>  <p>Tomba di ʿbd mlqrt figlio di [---]</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p><span class=\"lang\" lang=\"xpu-Latn\">ʿbdmlqrt</span> is a Phoenician personal name, “Servant of Melqart”.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> Campus 2020 60 </li><li> De Simone 2023 54 fig.3 </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> Line 1-4  20-62  Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
